19/12/2006
ATHENS, Greece -- Foreign Minister Dora Bakoyannis and Montenegrin counterpart Milan Rocen signed an agreement in Athens on Monday (December 18th) formally establishing diplomatic relations. Greece thus joins ten other countries with embassies in Europe's newest state. Bakoyannis also expressed her country's support for Montenegro's aspirations to join NATO and the EU.(Pobjeda, Vijesti, Kathimerini, Eleftherotypia - 19/12/06; ANA-MPA, AP - 18/12/06)
